author: reinhard
msg: Conditional GET (If-None-Match) support for ALL caching pipelines based on ETags. The ETag is the hex representation of the a pipeline's cache key hashcode.
Previously only cases where a cache key could be expressed as timestamp were supported (Last-Modified -> If-Modified-Since).

author: reinhard
msg: use MurmurHash 2.0, a strong hashing algorithm, to implement the hashCode() method of cache keys
[Using the Java MurmurHash 2.0 implementation by Andrzej Bialecki which is based on the original C version by Austin Appleby (http://murmurhash.googlepages.com/).]
